    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    dc:creator "Reverter-Gil, Oscar; Souto, Javier" ;
    dc:date "2015" ;
    dc:title "Redescription of some species of Bryozoa described by J. Jullien and L. Calvet in the NE Atlantic" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3788030>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3788034> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3788030>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. Lectotype of Hippothoa amoena Jullien & Calvet, 1903 (MOM INV-22578). A. Some autozooids. B. Group of irregular kenozooids. C. Primary orifice. D. Ovicell. E. Distal dietella." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3788030/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3788034>
    dc:description "Fig. 3. Pulpeirina amoena (Jullien & Calvet, 1903) comb. nov. (MOM INV-22580). A. Simple pores in a young, marginal autozooid. B. Tubular pores arranged radially. C. An autozooid with radially arranged tubular pores and a medial horizontal tubule. D. Inner view of an autozooid showing the tubular pseudopores and horizontal tubules. E. Detail showing tubular pores joining the horizontal tubule." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3788034/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

